  20 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  +files/beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-includefix.patch:
  Fixed missing include in plugin.h

  19 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r2.ebuild:
  Added default plugin set to PDEPEND.

  19 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org> files/beep-config:
  Added support for FAKE_XMMS_VERSION to beep-config.

*beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r2 (19 Oct 2004)

  19 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  -files/beep-media-player-0.9.6.1-gcc34.patch,
  -files/beep-media-player.desktop, -beep-media-player-0.9.6.1-r1.ebuild,
  -beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r1.ebuild,
  +beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r2.ebuild:
  Removing old version. Moved header files and setup symlinks to make more
  compatible with xmms plugins in the upcomming xmms-plugin.eclass.

  05 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  fixed multilib problems (bug #64580). Fixed mime options in .desktop (bug
  #65918). Fixed DEPEND (bug #65510).

  15 Sep 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  beep-media-player-0.9.6.1-r1.ebuild:
  Stable sparc.

  31 Aug 2004; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  -beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2.ebuild:
  Removing old ebuild and keeping stable 0.9.6.1-r1 around.

  31 Aug 2004; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Adding missing depend on libglade. Reported by both Tim Gurr (bug #62154) and
  Stefan Tittel (bug #61211).

*beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r1 (30 Aug 2004)

  30 Aug 2004; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +files/beep-config,
  +beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Add mmx and oss USE-flags. Enable more gnome functionality. Add beep-config to
  get more plugins building. ~amd64, no longer segfaults.

  30 Aug 2004; Luca Barbato <lu_zero@gentoo.org>
  beep-media-player-0.9.7_rc2.ebuild:
  Marked ~ppc

